---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/docs/Callout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { label: 'Documentation', href: '/odin/docs/introduction/overview' },
  { label: 'Roadmap' },
];

const headings = [
  { depth: 2, slug: 'completed', text: 'Completed' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'in-progress', text: 'In Progress' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'planned', text: 'Planned' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'future', text: 'Future' },
];
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Product Roadmap"
  description="Transparent development, continuous innovation. Track our progress and see what's coming next for Odin."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  headings={headings}
>

  <Callout type="tip" title="Want to Contribute?">
    <p>
      We welcome feature requests and contributions!
      <a href="https://github.com/dream-horizon-org/odin/issues/new" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Request a feature</a> or
      join the <a href="https://github.com/dream-horizon-org/odin/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">discussion</a>.
    </p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="in-progress">In Progress</h2>

  <h3>Parallel Operations on Components <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q1</span></h3>
  <p>
    Execute operations across multiple components of a service simultaneously, dramatically reducing deployment and management time.
    Enables concurrent scaling, updates, and lifecycle operations with intelligent dependency handling and failure isolation.
  </p>

  <h3>Robust State Transition with Enhanced Locking <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q1</span></h3>
  <p>
    Reliable state machine management for component and service lifecycles with distributed locking mechanisms. Prevents race conditions
    and ensures atomic state transitions across concurrent operations, providing consistency guarantees even in highly parallel environments.
  </p>

  <h3>Fine-Grained Authorization Capabilities <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q1</span></h3>
  <p>
    Granular access control for environments, services, and components with role-based and attribute-based policies. Define precise
    permissions for teams and individuals, controlling who can deploy, scale, or modify specific resources across your infrastructure.
  </p>

  <h3>Custom Request Interceptors <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q1</span></h3>
  <p>
    Extensible middleware hooks for intercepting and modifying deployment requests on the fly. Transform configurations, inject
    environment-specific values, validate inputs, or apply custom business logic before operations execute.
  </p>

  <h3>Odin Events <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q1</span></h3>
  <p>
    Event-driven architecture exposing all deployment lifecycle events for external consumption. Subscribe to deployment, scaling,
    and state change events to build custom CI/CD pipelines, trigger notifications, or integrate with external automation systems.
  </p>

  <h3>Expanding Component Registry <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q1</span></h3>
  <p>
    Growing library of production-grade infrastructure components following the Odin Component Interface (OCI) specification.
    Check out the <a href="https://github.com/dream-horizon-org/odin-components" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Odin Components Repository</a> to
    explore supported components and track new components currently in development.
  </p>

  <h2 id="planned">Planned</h2>

  <h3>Secrets Management <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q3</span></h3>
  <p>
    Integrated secrets management with vault support and encryption. Securely manage sensitive configuration with rotation policies,
    audit logging, and integration with HashCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, and Azure Key Vault.
  </p>

  <h3>Odin Log Command <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q2</span></h3>
  <p>
    Unified log access for deployed services and components directly from the CLI. Retrieve historical
    entries for post-deployment audits, debugging, and troubleshooting across all environments.
  </p>

  <h3>Odin Analytics Dashboard <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q2</span></h3>
  <p>
    Comprehensive analytics interface for tracking deployment metrics, environment health, and Odin system performance. Visualize
    deployment frequency, success rates, environment utilization, and platform health with actionable insights and historical trends.
  </p>

  <h3>Service Set Support <span style="color: var(--text-tertiary); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.875rem;">2025 Q2</span></h3>
  <p>
    Group related services into logical sets for coordinated deployments and management. Deploy, update, or operate on multiple
    services as a single unit while maintaining individual service autonomy and versioning.
  </p>

  <h2 id="future">Future</h2>

  <h3>AI-Powered Insights</h3>
  <p>
    Intelligent recommendations for optimization, cost reduction, and performance. Machine learning models analyze your deployment
    patterns and provide actionable insights for improving reliability and reducing costs.
  </p>

  <h3>AI-Powered Service Onboarding</h3>
  <p>
    Streamlined service onboarding with AI-assisted configuration generation. Automatically analyze your application code, detect
    dependencies, and generate optimized service definitions with minimal manual input.
  </p>

  <h3>Environment Cloning</h3>
  <p>
    Instantly replicate entire environments with a single command. Clone production to staging, create isolated testing environments,
    or spin up developer sandboxes with full service configurations and data snapshots.
  </p>

  <Callout type="note" title="Roadmap is Subject to Change">
    <p>
      Our roadmap is based on community feedback and evolving needs. Timelines are estimates and features may be adjusted based on
      priorities. Have a feature request? <a href="https://github.com/ds-horizon/odin/issues/new" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Let us know!</a>
    </p>
  </Callout>

  <hr />

  <div class="cta-section">
    <h2>Want to Influence the Roadmap?</h2>
    <p>
      We're building Odin for teams like yours. Share your feedback, request features, or contribute to development.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-buttons">
      <a href="https://github.com/ds-horizon/odin/issues/new" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Request a Feature
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/ds-horizon/odin/discussions" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Join Discussion
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .cta-section {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .cta-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: var(--line-height-snug);
  }

  .cta-section p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
  }

  .cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.875rem 1.75rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    transition: all var(--transition-base);
    text-decoration: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--primary-red);
    color: var(--text-white);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    border: 1px solid transparent;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--primary-red-hover);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    background: var(--bg-white);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-medium);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .btn-secondary:hover {
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
    border-color: var(--text-primary);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cta-section {
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .cta-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .cta-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .btn {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 300px;
    }
  }
</style>
